WEBVTT

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:45.000
Interviewer: Let's discuss active listening first.

00:00:45.000 --> 00:01:30.000
Candidate: Sure. I understand the customer clearly by giving them my full attention. I avoid misunderstandings through careful paraphrasing. I build trust by being genuine. And I respond appropriately to their needs.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:02:00.000
Interviewer: And your communication style?

00:02:00.000 --> 00:03:00.000
Candidate: I use clear language. I avoid jargon. I am always polite. And I explain the next steps to keep customers informed.

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:30.000
Interviewer: How about complaints?

00:03:30.000 --> 00:04:15.000
Candidate: I stay calm during difficult conversations. I listen carefully to the complaint. I acknowledge the issue openly. And I look for a solution that satisfies everyone.

00:04:15.000 --> 00:04:45.000
Interviewer: What do you look for in a solution?

00:04:45.000 --> 00:05:30.000
Candidate: It addresses the issue completely. It is realistic and achievable. It is explained clearly. And it is delivered in a timely way.

00:05:30.000 --> 00:06:00.000
Interviewer: Professional conduct?

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:45.000
Candidate: I always have a respectful attitude. Punctuality matters to me greatly. I value polite communication. And I embrace responsibility in all tasks.

00:06:45.000 --> 00:07:15.000
Interviewer: Managing pressure?

00:07:15.000 --> 00:08:00.000
Candidate: I stay calm. I prioritize tasks effectively. I communicate clearly under stress. And I focus on solutions always.
